   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422598_1828_03_12_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworths Town</placeName>
                  <lb/>
                  <date when="1828-03-12">March 12<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1828</date>
               </dateline>
               <lb/>
            </opener>
            <p>I hear with much regret<lb/>
               for <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#IE">my country</placeName> and for<lb/>
               my own family, who had<lb/>
               hoped to cultivate his<lb/>
               society that <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SpriT1">M<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi>Spring Rice</persName>
               <lb/>
               is going to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#II">India</placeName>-<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>Surely he will not - he<lb/>
               cannot go without at least<lb/>
               writing to me to tell me<lb/>
               whether this appointment<lb/>
               is for his benefit - the only<lb/>
               circumstance that could<lb/>
               console me for the loss we<lb/>
               in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#IE">Ireland</placeName> must sustain<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>He will write I am <choice>
                  <orig>per-<lb/>
               suaded</orig>
                  <reg>persuaded</reg>
               </choice> to tell me whether<lb/>
               he is satisfied that the <choice>
                  <orig>sa-<lb/>
                  crifice</orig>
                  <reg>sacrifice</reg>
               </choice> he is making is<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422598_1828_03_12_page02.jpg"/>
               
               necessary - Does he take<lb/>
               his family with him?<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>He will feel that these<lb/>
               questions are from one<lb/>
               whose esteem &amp; regard<lb/>
               for him justify their<lb/>
               abruptness -<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
               his sincere friend<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
               <note>Miss Edgeworth</note>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
         </div>
      </body>
